        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 3:52PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>Showers and isolated thunderstorms will continue through 500 PM CDT
across northwestern Ogle and southwestern Winnebago Counties.
Conditions are favorable for funnel clouds with these showers. In
rare occasions, these funnel clouds can briefly reach the ground as
a weak landspout tornado. If they occur, these type of landspouts
tend to weak, brief, and tend to produce minimal damage.

If threatening weather approaches, seek shelter indoors.

Locations impacted include...
Forreston, Pecatonica, Adeline, Winnebago, Baileyville, and Seward.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
